27/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Landslides have killed at least eight people in northern Turkey. 
Rivers swamped their banks in Rize province after torrential rains hit the region, Governor Seyfullah Hacimuftuoglu said on Friday (August 27th). 
Six people are reported missing after a landslide struck the Black Sea town of Gundogan early Friday. 
Seven people have been rescued. 
(Cumhurriyet, AP, Hurriyet, AFP - 27/08/10)

